Full Title: Introduction to the Social and Cultural Environment
Description: An introduction to the relationship of societies and the environment from prehistorical times to the present. The course is global in perspective, and includes history, literature, philosophy, economics, science, and culture as evidence for examining the human social environment.

Units: 4.0
Grading: Optional

Full Title: Introduction to the Social and Cultural Environment - Honors
Description: Honors section designed for highly motivated students to receive one unit of additional honors credit. Requires one hour per week of in-depth analysis and discussion of the social and cultural environments with course instructor and completion of a related project.
PreRequisite: Concurrent enrollment in ENV S 3; Consent of instructor.
College: L&S
Units: 1.0
Grading: Pass/No Pass
